    {
      "text": "Laura's Happy Adventures is a 1998 adventure game developed by Ubi Soft Montreal and published by Ubi Soft, released as part of the Playmobil Interactive series of products. The setting is based on Playmobil's Victorian dollhouse line. The game's storyline revolves around a good-natured young girl named Laura as she solves the mystery of a magic diamond by helping the people around her. A Game Boy Color-exclusive version, simply re-titled Laura, was produced and released in 2000.",
